    <h2 class="section-label">The break</h2>
    <section class="section-body">
      <p>After 12.5 years, my run at Meta ended in a round of layoffs &mdash; a dozen-plus years on developer infrastructure, and now, for the first time in a long while, a clean pause. Time to reset, reflect, and be around for my kid while the days still feel long.</p>
    </section>

    <h2 class="section-label">What&rsquo;s next</h2>
    <section class="section-body">
      <p>No hurry, but listening. I&rsquo;m open to what comes next &mdash; early-stage startups especially, where the team is small, the ownership is real, and the infrastructure gets built from scratch instead of maintained at scale. If that sounds like you, <a href="mailto:junz@junz.info">say hello</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <h2 class="section-label">At home</h2>
    <section class="section-body">
      <p>Pouring the spare hours back into the house &mdash; a run of improvement projects, and a home gym I&rsquo;m kitting out piece by piece.</p>
    </section>

    <h2 class="section-label">Playing again</h2>
    <section class="section-body">
      <p>Picking up video games after a few years away &mdash; turns out a young kid and a backlog don&rsquo;t mix. The backlog, of course, is still right where I left it.</p>
